), 
<collectingCountry box="[568,681,223,249]" name="Colombia" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[694,787,223,249]" name="Ecuador" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[844,895,223,249]" name="Peru" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[912,1035,223,249]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1047,1106,223,249]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref72890" refString="Haig, J. (1968) Eastern Pacific expeditions of the New York Zoological Society. Porcellanid crabs (Crustacea: Anomura) from the west coast of tropical America. Zoologica, New York, 53 (2), 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1968">1968</bibRefCitation>
; García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu- Sánchez 2009; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moscoso, V." box="[322,490,259,285]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref75462" refString="Moscoso, V. (2012) Catalogo de crustaceos decapodos y estomatopodos del Peru. Boletin Instituto del Mar del Peru, 27 (1 / 2), 1 - 208. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 4563" type="journal article" year="2012">Moscoso 2012</bibRefCitation>
; present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="110.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,295,321]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Ecology</emphasis>
. Intertidal and shallow subtidal, known depth range: 
<quantity box="[890,963,295,321]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="0.0">0–7 m</quantity>
; under rocks, in crevices of rocks and corals, sometimes associated with hermit crabs, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson" authorityName="Stimpson" box="[662,968,331,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Aniculus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[662,854,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Aniculus elegans</emphasis>
Stimpson
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[984,1107,331,357]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 440" refId="ref72816" refString="Haig, J. (1960) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Anomura) of the Eastern Pacific. Allan Hancock Pacific Expedition, 24, 1 - 440." type="journal article" year="1960">Haig 1960</bibRefCitation>
; García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu- Sánchez 2009; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moscoso, V." box="[322,491,367,393]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 208" refId="ref75462" refString="Moscoso, V. (2012) Catalogo de crustaceos decapodos y estomatopodos del Peru. Boletin Instituto del Mar del Peru, 27 (1 / 2), 1 - 208. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 4563" type="journal article" year="2012">Moscoso 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="110" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="110.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,403,429]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Remarks</emphasis>
. In all Panamanian specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nobili" authorityYear="1901" box="[678,807,403,428]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Petrolisthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ortmanni">
<emphasis box="[678,807,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">P. ortmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[821,903,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 68" captionStartId="109.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@109.[179,1407,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURE 68. Petrolisthes ortmanni Nobili, 1901: A, B, ovigerous female (cl 6.0 mm, cw 6.4 mm) from Las Perlas Islands, Panama (MZUSP 33808), dorsal (A) and ventral (B) views [photographs by AA]; C, female (cl 4.2 mm, cw 4.1 mm) from the same locality (FLMNH UF 57157), dorsal view [photograph courtesy of Paulo P.G. Pachelle]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5532379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5532379/files/figure.png" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
), the carapace and P1 varies from pale brownish to yellowish, whereas the P2–P4 are always darker brown. In some younger individuals from 
<collectingCountry box="[1200,1313,439,465]" name="Colombia" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, the P1 are paler and speckled with dark spots (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, L. A. A. &amp; Santana-Moreno, L. D. &amp; Anker, A." box="[557,781,475,501]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" pagination="576 - 588" refId="ref71402" refString="Ferreira, L. A. A., Santana-Moreno, L. D. &amp; Anker, A. (2020) A new species of the porcelain crab genus Petrolisthes from the Pacific coast of Panama, with taxonomic notes on closely related species (Decapoda: Anomura: Porcellanidae). Zootaxa, 4858 (4), 576 - 588. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4858.4.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Ferreira 
<emphasis box="[655,713,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen illustrated by García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu- Sánchez (2009) was photographed either 
<emphasis box="[631,773,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">post-mortem</emphasis>
or shortly after preservation and lost most of its original colours.
</paragraph>
